Paul: Merrill is out with this on TYC today FWIW: Tyco (TYC; $13.73; D-2-3-7)
Updated Sum-of-Parts Valuation Analysis Sep02E$2.09 03E$2.40
• Tyco's near-term profits and margins may not fully reflect both ultimate
distraction costs and the requirement to focus resources more on driving
organic growth.
• We think, however, that sales versus profits should be more insulated from
downside risk due to Tyco's broad geographic and customer end markets.
• diversified product base, high recurring revenues and customized products.
• We therefore took another cut at our "Sum-of-the-Parts" analysis using only
Enterprise Value/Sales and reduced debt following CIT's IPO.
• Our analysis yields a median value estimate per TYC share of $31 using 5-year
average peer multiples, and $27 using current multiples. Our forecast could be
conservative as we have assigned higher current net debt levels and the
electronics industry could begin to rebound next year.
• The market may opt to wait for the arrival of a new management team (an event
that could be many months away) before it begins to treat Tyco's valuation more
in line with peer averages, we believe. In the interim, the stock could remain
extremely volatile. Still, even if current and new management were to
principally pursue a strategy of liquidation, our analysis suggests there would
appear to be substantial valuation upside from present levels. (J. Inch)
