recently upgraded to buy.
My view on analyst research is to read for facts, insights and
perspective...and not to blindly follow rec's. A good research report can tip
you off to issues and considerations it would take quite awhile to dig out on
your own. Often reports contain data from user/vendor surveys that would be too
costly to do or buy. OTOH, the investor must be aware that IB relationships or
other incentives could distort the views of the analyst and thus to expect a
somewhat bullish bias..especially where IB relationships exist.
