Date:7/16/2002 1:38:17 PM
From:Bob Rudd
Good list, Timba. I tend to look at some of the following:
1. Insider activity
2. Short interest - high levels can mean fundamental shorts, doing thorough
research, have uncovered some stinky stuff.
3. EV/EBITDA, EV/EBITDA-CAPEX, EV/FCF The EV adjusts for debt & cash levels
which price multiples do not...thus producing lower multiples for debt ridden
companies.
4. Competition & competitive position. Hoovers or quicken compare can be good
sources for competitor info as is 10-k.
5. Receivable & inventory vs sales compared to PY QTR.
6. Spreads...trading liquidity...avoid excessive spreads.
7. Message boards...sometimes there are well informed posters that can and will
point out key issues As an example, here's a response I got today on an inquiry
on ICN
http://messages.yahoo.com/bbs?.mm=FN&action=m&board=7076916&tid=icn&sid=7076916
mid=26506
Depending on what I see, I may look at other factors as as well.
